div.div:
Add partial payment feature and update various functions/classes
Including the feature for partial payments, the previous functions for layouts and models have been updated accordingly. Also, the 'findByUsername' function in the ApiController is changed to use email instead of username. The larecipe.php file's default version has been refactored from 1.0 to 1.1, and relevant files have been renamed accordingly. Besides, several miscellaneous updates have been made across the code for cleanup and consistency with implemented alterations.

Add OTP generation and email notification functionality
This commit modifies the ApiController to generate a One-Time Password (OTP) during the login process and send notification email to the user's email address. The OTP is saved along with user details and expiry time for further validation. An additional method, generateNumericToken, has been introduced to handle OTP generation. The sequence of sending notifications has also been adjusted accordingly.

API: Implement One-Time Password validation for login
This commit restructures the login process in the ApiController that now requires One-Time Password (OTP) verification. Additionally, it replaces all instances of 'username' with 'email' in the login process, thus switching from username-based to email-based authentication. In the same vein, a validateOtp method has been added to handle OTP validation. Changes in routes and middleware have also been made to accommodate these adjustments.

Fixed Single-instance EventBus in the Android App In this commit, a bug related to the Single-instance EventBus in the Android app has been fixed. This bug was causing the EventBus to create multiple instances in some scenarios. Now, the EventBus correctly maintains a single instance throughout the application, as intended.

Add calendar event functionality and change input type in ShopProductEdit
Implemented CRUD operations for calendar events in CalendarController and added permissions to the app's framework. Changed Quill input type to regular text area for product descriptions in ShopProductEdit for simplified configuration and enhanced user experience. New routes also added to api.php for these operations. A new table and model have been created to handle Calendar Events.
